# Force Vercel's Python builder to install from requirements.txt (a plain
# `pip install -r`, no project self-build) instead of the uv manifests. The repo
# never installs itself (Docker uses `--no-install-project`; pyproject has no
# [build-system]), so excluding these keeps the deploy predictable. Local
# dev/Docker/uv are unaffected — the files stay in the repo, just not uploaded.
pyproject.toml
uv.lock
